<span id="freeTextContainer3568309800857920985">Very well researched and written .book. For any follower of the Vendée Globe or Ocean Racing this is a must read. I started following the VG in 2008/09 so it was really great to go back to 96/97 and learn more of the history of this extremely extreme sport .<br/><br/>I especially like how the author related his own experiences of sailing offshore and that he did so in such an honest way. A nice touch to start and end the book with . I have really enjoyed reading this book while watching the VG . I highly </span>
  <span id="freeText3568309800857920985" style="display:none">Very well researched and written .book. For any follower of the Vendée Globe or Ocean Racing this is a must read. I started following the VG in 2008/09 so it was really great to go back to 96/97 and learn more of the history of this extremely extreme sport .<br /><br />I especially like how the author related his own experiences of sailing offshore and that he did so in such an honest way. A nice touch to start and end the book with . I have really enjoyed reading this book while watching the VG . I highly recommend !<br /><br />I’ve worked decades on boats , mostly sail including transoceanic , although not southern ocean, and I feel this author has really nailed the trials and tribulations . When people ask what it’s like I always tell them it’s worse than they can imagine and also much better. If you plan passages prudently then weather is fairer than foul and most of the time it may be uncomfortable but not dangerous. But for those seat of the pants times there’s no amount of money that can compensate for the misery. !<br /><br />Being a fellow Canadian I was especially captivated by the story of Gerry Rouf which sadly ended tragically. As far as rescue attempts I can’t overstate how dangerous if not impossible it is , to turn around into a head-sea and bash your way back upwind. Even with all the will in the world ....</span>
